    <note>Yao(1) Bao [25092] He rose to be a general and died in battle against the Tangut. The family seems to have been a hereditary military elite who protected their Inner Mongolian (Suiyuan) prefecture against Tangut incursions. The funerary inscription was drafted 35 years after Bao's death in response to a request from his sons, Si [25093] and Lin [25094]. Su Song, WJ, 54.17a-21a. CBD, 2, 1717.</note>
